<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870819-0031 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Tri-State Motor Transit Co.</HL><DD> 08/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TSM CEXXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Tri-State Motor Transit Co. said it broke off merger talks with Circle Express Inc.    Tri-State, a Joplin, Mo.-based trucking company, said it intends &quot;to remain as an independent company at this time&quot; but declined to give any additional details about its talks with Circle.    As previously reported, Tri-State said Circle, an Indianapolis-based trucking concern, sought early last month to discuss a possible merger. According to Tri-State, Circle said it was interested in acquiring Tri-State stock for &quot;a significant premium over the current market value.&quot; At the time, Arthur L. Belford, Circle's chairman, said no offer had been made. Mr. Belford didn't return several telephone calls yesterday.    In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Tri-State closed at $19.375 a share, down $1.75. In national over-the-counter trading, Circle Express closed at $9.875 a share, down 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>